---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import profilePhoto from '../images/profile.jpg';
---
<Layout title="Jaewon Hur">
	<div class="hero">
		<div class="hero-text">
			<h1>Jaewon Hur</h1>
			<p>
				Hi :&#41; I'm Jaewon, a new college grad from Univeristy of California, Berkeley with a Bachelor's degree in Electrical Engineering & Computer Science (EECS).
				I'm interested in building hardware, VLSI design, and computer architecture.
			</p>
			<p>
				During my undergrad, I've done research in spatial architecture and tensor algebra abstractions at <a href="https://slice.eecs.berkeley.edu">SLICE Lab</a> under Professor <a href="https://www2.eecs.berkeley.edu/Faculty/Homepages/cwfletcher.html">Chris Fletcher</a>.
				I'm currently working at the lab continuing my research in building a custom flexible spatial architecture for ML applications targeting FlashAttention and CNNs.
				Before the joining the lab, I participated in the 16nm SoC Tapeout project sponsored by Intel and Apple, working on designing and developing a DMA engine for DSP workloads.
			</p>
		</div>
		<Image src={profilePhoto} alt="Jaewon Hur" width={280} height={350} densities={[1, 2, 3]} class="profile-photo" />
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	:global(main) {
		max-width: 880px;
	}

	.hero {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: space-between;
		gap: 2rem;
	}

	.hero-text {
		flex: 1;
	}

	.hero-text h1 {
		margin-top: 0;
	}

	.profile-photo {
		display: block;
		flex-shrink: 0;
		width: 280px;
		height: 350px;
		object-fit: cover;
		padding: 4px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 640px) {
		.hero {
			flex-direction: column-reverse;
		}
	}
</style>
